<p>I want to count and aggregate(sum) a column in a <code>data.table</code>, and couldn't find the most efficient way to do this.  This seems to be close to what I want <a href="http://stackoverflow.com/questions/16513827/r-summarizing-multiple-columns-with-data-table">R summarizing multiple columns with data.table</a>.</p>  <p>My data:</p>  <pre><code>set.seed(321) dat &lt;- data.table(MNTH = c(rep(201501, 4), rep(201502, 3), rep(201503, 5),                            rep(201504, 4)),     VAR = sample(c(0,1), 16, replace=T))  &gt; dat      MNTH VAR  1: 201501   1  2: 201501   1  3: 201501   0  4: 201501   0  5: 201502   0  6: 201502   0  7: 201502   0  8: 201503   0  9: 201503   0 10: 201503   1 11: 201503   1 12: 201503   0 13: 201504   1 14: 201504   0 15: 201504   1 16: 201504   0 </code></pre>  <p>I want to both count and sum <code>VAR</code> by <code>MNTH</code> using data.table. The desired result:</p>  <pre><code>    MNTH COUNT VAR 1 201501     4   2 2 201502     3   0 3 201503     5   2 4 201504     4   2 </code></pre>